name: RO-ProcTankSpaceplane
title: Tank [Procedural, Shielded]
description: Heat-shielded switchable procedural tank with heat shielded Includes normal (Structural), highly pressurized (Fuselage), and cryogenic tank options. Rated for LEO reentries on a spaceplane.

name: proceduralAvionics
title: Avionics [Procedural]
description: This is a procedural avionics unit.  It simply contains a battery and avionics control, so don't forget to add an antenna.

name: proceduralBattery
title: Procedural Battery (Deprecated)
description: DO NOT USE THIS. Use Service Modules instead

name: proceduralCrewTube
title: Crew Tube [Procedural]
description: Air tight pressure hull protected by a thick layer of Kevlar and carbon nanofiber blankets to provide protection against micro-meteorites as well as thermal insulation and limited radiation shielding. These parts provide safe and structurally intact internal spaces to allow crew to move between crewed parts.

name: proceduralNoseCone
title: Nose Cone [Procedural]
description: Made from viscoelastic nanopolymers (which were discovered by accident... growing in the back of the office mini-fridge) this nose cone can be stretched to fit a range of diameters, and can be made more or less pointy. Hardens to a rigid structure before launch!

name: proceduralSRBRealFuels
title: Solid Rocket Motor [Procedural]
description: Made from viscoelastic nanopolymers (which were discovered by accident... growing in the back of the office mini-fridge) this solid rocket can be stretched to accommodate fuel loads of a range of sizes and shapes. Can be optimized for sea-level or high altitude uses. Hardens to a rigid structure before launch! Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: proceduralStackDecoupler
title: Decoupler [Procedural]
description: Made from viscoelastic nanopolymers (which were discovered by accident... growing in the back of the office mini-fridge) this decoupler can be stretched to accommodate a range of sizes.

name: proceduralStructural
title: Structure [Procedural]
description: Made from viscoelastic nanopolymers (which were discovered by accident... growing in the back of the office mini-fridge) this structural element can be stretched to range of sizes and shapes. Hardens to a rigid structure before launch!

name: proceduralTankRealFuels
title: Tank [Procedural]
description: Switchable procedural tank. Comes in various levels of insulation, rigid/balloon, and pressurized/highly-pressurized forms. Defaults to type Default but can be switched to other types in the part popup menu.
